{"key":"post-15097750","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>15097750</id>\n<content>The reason for misting several times over the first few hours is to avoid washing the dry verm off.&amp;nbsp; If you mist heavily right away, much of the verm will be gone.&amp;nbsp; Misting slightly a few times hydrates it slowly, thus leaving it in place.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;From then on, you mist as required to replace the moisture that is lost to evaporation.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>15097758</next>\n<prev>15097660</prev>\n<first>15097660</first>\n<last>15097758</last>\n<when>1316397162</when>\n<utime>09/19/11 04:52 AM</utime>\n</post>"}